title: Ratio of Loans and Discounts to Individual Deposits, National Banks, Total for United States
notes:
Monthly Coverage Varies From Year To Year. Except For 1870, Which Only Has Data For Four Months, All Years 1871-1914 Have Scattered Five Month Coverage. Six Months Are Presented For 1915. See Original Series On "Loans And Discounts" And "Individual Deposits" Except That Here, "Clearing-House Exchanges" Have Been Deducted From The Latter. Source: Computed By NBER From Data In Annual Reports Of The Comptroller Of The Currency.
